						               													<description>Set in the whimsical alternate Victorian era of Pax Limpopo, players bet on races where street urchins jockeys race their velociraptor mounts through the London sewers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player secretly fills out a betting card placing bets on first, second, and third place.  They also get a random chit specifying a particular racer as first or last place.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the race itself, players influence the outcome of the races by playing from hands of ordinary playing cards to move raptors, and/or attack other raptors until the race is won.  Then players collect rewards according to their wagers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Three races are run, and the overall winner is the bettor with the most money at the end.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is available either as rules only, in a kit with 6 velociraptor racers, or as a kit with the racers and a molded rubber track and winners' stand.  The rules contain all you need if you wish to make your own components, but the components themselves are excellent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
